To show data from Firebase in your `FutureMK` component, you can use the `useState` and `useEffect` hooks to fetch data from Firestore and update your component state.

Here's an example of how you could do this:

```
import { Text, View, Image, Pressable } from 'react-native';
import { gStyle } from '../styles/style';
import React, {useState, useEffect} from 'react';
import { useNavigation } from '@react-navigation/native';
import {firebase} from '../Firebase/firebase'

export default function FutureMK() {
    const navigation = useNavigation();
    const [posts, setPosts] = useState([]);

    useEffect(() => {
        const db = firebase.firestore();
        const unsubscribe = db.collection('FutureMK').onSnapshot(snapshot => {
            const newPosts = snapshot.docs.map(doc => ({
                id: doc.id,
                ...doc.data()
            }));
            setPosts(newPosts);
        });
        return unsubscribe;
    }, []);

    return (
        <View style={gStyle.main}>
            {posts.map(post => (
                <View style={gStyle.mainFMK} key={post.id}>
                    <Text style={gStyle.dateFutureMK}>{post.time}</Text>
                    <View style={gStyle.FutureMKimg}>
                        <Image source={{uri: post.image}} style={gStyle.FutureMKbannerImg}/>
                        <Text style={gStyle.FutureMKnameOfMK}>{post.name}</Text>
                        <Text style={gStyle.hr}></Text>
                    </View>
                    <Text style={gStyle.FutureMKprice}>Цена: <Text style={gStyle.FutureMKrub}>{post.price}</Text></Text>
                    <Text style={gStyle.FutureMKdescription}>
                        {post.description}
                    </Text>
                    <Pressable style={gStyle.FutureMKmoreDetails} 
                        onPress={() => {
                            navigation.navigate('SignUpForMK', {post});
                        }}
                    >
                        <Text style={gStyle.FutureMKbtnTxt}>Подробнее</Text>
                    </Pressable>
                    <Text style={gStyle.FutureMKline}></Text>
                </View>
            ))}
        </View>
    );
}
```

In this code, we're setting up a state variable called `posts` to store an array of post objects retrieved from Firebase. We're using the `useEffect` hook to fetch data from the `FutureMK` collection in Firestore and update our state with the retrieved post data. 

We're then mapping over the `posts` array to render each post as a separate component in the return statement. Inside the `View` for each post, we're displaying the `name`, `time`, `image`, `price`, and `description` fields fetched from Firestore and displaying a "Подробнее" button that navigates to the `SignUpForMK` screen with the selected post object.

