The security rules for Firebase Cloud Firestore and Firebase Cloud Storage are separate, so modifying your Cloud Firestore security rules won't affect your Cloud Storage rules.

To update your Cloud Storage security rules to allow all users to read your data, you can use the following code:

```
// Allow all users to read from any bucket and file
service firebase.storage {
  match /b/{bucket}/o {
    match /{allPaths=**} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.token.admin == true;
    }
  }
}
```

This code sets up a wildcard rule that allows any user to read from any bucket and file, but only authenticated users with an `admin` token to write to the bucket and files.

Make sure to test and validate your security rules to ensure that they meet your application's security requirements and prevent unauthorized access to your database and storage.
